peopleAlsoAsk.question: How much is a penny from 1924 worth today?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: The value of a 1924 Wheat Penny depends on its condition and mint mark. Circulated coins without a mint mark are generally worth about 15 cents to $2. The 1924-D (Denver) variant in circulated condition can range from $20 to over $100, and the 1924-S (San Francisco) from $1 to $10.
